<div id="banner">
	<h1>&#8220;I think there is a</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>&#8220;I think there is a world market for maybe five computers.&#8221; - Thomas Watson Senior, Chairman of IBM, 1943.<p /><p />Now that we have global networks, perhaps Dr. Watson <a href="http://philip.greenspun.com/internet-application-workbook/distributed-computing">was off by four</a>&#8230;or four million.<p /><p />The future will be made of thousands of small pieces&mdash;computers, protocols, programming languages and people&mdash;all working together. We need to stop worrying about how to make everyone <a href="http://www.passport.com/">do the same thing</a>, and instead work on how to <a href="http://www.plexnow.com/">connect</a> the (<a href="http://www.w3.org/DesignIssues/UI">not so</a>) different things that people do <a href="http://www.w3.org/Addressing/schemes">together</a>.</p>

<p class="posted">posted January 14, 2002 04:31 PM (<a class="category" href="cat_"></a>)  <a href="000111" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

